und 2===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 10 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = North Shore\n| score = 3-16\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Championships Continue/City V North Shore\n| page =5\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17158\n| date = 1919-05-12\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190512.2.21.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>\n| away = City\n| try1 = L Boon\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = H Wynn, [[Tom Haddon]], G Reed, Clarke\n| con2 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Devonport Domain 1\n| attendance = 500\n| referee = J Eddowes\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 10 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Maritime\n| score = 19-18\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Championships Continue/Maritime Beats Newton/Margin of One Point/Newton V Maritime\n| page =5\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17158\n| date = 1919-05-12\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190512.2.21.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>| away = Newton\n| try1 = Sheehan, [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]] 3, A Sutton\n| con1 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[George Isles]] 2, [[Wally Somers]], Mansill, Miller, Keenan\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Auckland Domain\n| attendance = 4000\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 10 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Grafton\n| score = 26-6\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Championships Continue/Marist Old Boys V Grafton\n| page =5\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17158\n| date = 1919-05-12\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190512.2.21.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>| away = Marist\n| try1 = [[Karl Ifwersen]] 3, Mitchell, Osborne, [[Ernie Herring]]\n| con1 = [[Karl Ifwersen]] 4\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = McDevitt, Casey\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Devonport Domain 2\n| attendance =\n| referee = T Hill\n}}\n \n===Round 3===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 17 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 12-10\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =City Defeats Newton/City V Newton\n| page =7\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17164\n| date = 1919-05-19\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190519.2.91.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>| away = Newton\n| try1 = B Paki, [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| con1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]]\n| pen1 = [[Bill Davidson (rugby league)|Bill Davidson]] 2\n| try2 = Condon, [[Bill Williams (rugby league)|Bill Williams]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = Phil Castles\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance =\n| referee = Eddowes\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 17 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Maritime\n| score = 11-5\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Maritime V Grafton\n| page =7\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17164\n| date = 1919-05-19\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190519.2.91.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>\n| away = Grafton\n| try1 = A Sutton, Cargill, [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]]\n| con1 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]]\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Bill Walsh (rugby league)|Bill Walsh]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = Unknown x 1 mark\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance =\n| referee = Vause\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 17 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = North Shore\n| score = 6-8\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =North Shore V Ponsonby\n| page =7\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17164\n| date = 1919-05-19\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190519.2.91.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>\n| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = [[Archie Waddell]], [[Stan Walters (rugby league)|Stan Walters]]\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Jim Clark (rugby league)|Jim Clark]], [[Bill Walsh (rugby league)|Bill Walsh]]\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = Halliday\n| stadium = Devonport Domain 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = Len Farrant\n}}\n\n===Round 4===\nThere was confusion with the Round 4 draw with the newspapers listing the match between North Shore and Maritime when in fact it was Newton who were supposed to be the opponent. As a result, Newton players did not arrive at the ground. Eventually Newton found enough substitutes but they still began the game 2-3 players short. In spite of this they still managed to win by 14 points to 9. Also the City team took the field with 6 juniors while Grafton had 2 juniors and played a man short. The chief issue was with the New Zealand team touring Australia at the time meaning many key players were absent from their club teams.\n\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 31 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Newton\n| score = 14-9\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Newton Defeats North Shore/Newton V North Shore\n| page =8\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17176\n| date = 1919-06-02\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190602.2.119.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>| away = North Shore\n| try1 = A Isles, Keenan 2, [[George Isles]]\n| con1 =\n| pen1 = A Isles\n| try2 = Ernie Bailey\n| con2 = McAneny\n| pen2 = McAneny & 1 mark\n| stadium = Victoria Park 1\n| attendance = 2500\n| referee = A Ball\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 31 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 25-2\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Grafton Outpointed by City/City V Grafton\n| page =8\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17176\n| date = 1919-06-02\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190602.2.119.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>| away = Grafton\n| try1 = Hogan, H Wynn, Cole, Asher, [[Jim Clark (rugby league)|Jim Clark]] 2, G Reed\n| con1 = Asher 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = W Ghent\n| stadium = Victoria Park 2\n| attendance = 2500\n| referee = [[William Wynyard (rugby league)|William Wynyard]]\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 31 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = Postponed\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Newton Defeats North Shore\n| page =8\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17176\n| date = 1919-06-02\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190602.2.119.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>| away = Marist\n| try1 =\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium =\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n===Round 5===\nIn the match at Devonport the Marist team was led from the field by their captain with the score at 9-0 to North Shore in protest at a refereeing decision. During the round 5 match between [[Marist Saints|Marist]] and [[North Shore Albions|North Shore]] the [[Marist Saints|Marist]] team left the field early in protest against the referee. After hearing the report of referee Cleal, and a statement from McDevett, the Marist captain it was decided to suspend McDevett for 12 months after it was he who had told the referee that he would be taking his team from the field in protest and proceeded to do so.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 15-6\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Ponsonby United Wins Comfortably/Nine Points Margin Over Maritime\n| page =8\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume L, Issue 136\n| date = 1919-06-09\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19190609.2.109\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>\n| away = Maritime\n| try1 = McGregor, O\u2019Brien, Cadman\n| con1 = McGregor, D Norgrove\n| pen1 = McGregor\n| try2 = A Sutton, Beecham\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park 1\n| attendance = 5000\n| referee = [[William Wynyard (rugby league)|William Wynyard]]\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = North Shore\n| score = 9-0\n| report = <ref name=\"ponsby_united\">{{cite news\n| title =Ponsonby United Wins Comfortably/Nine Points Margin Over Maritime/Grafton\u2019s Default\n| page =8\n| publisher = Auckland Star, Volume L, Issue 136\n| date = 1919-06-09\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19190609.2.109\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>\n| away = Marist\n| try1 = Nelson, Emirali, Griffin\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Devonport Domain\n| attendance =\n| referee = Cleal\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Newton\n| score = WBD-LBD\n| report = <ref name=\"ponsby_united\" />\n| away = Grafton\n| try1 =\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park 2\n| attendance =\n| referee = J Ball\n}}\n\n===Round 6===\nGrafton were not able to field a full team and were reinforced by players from Newton who had a bye. This was done so that they would not be forced to drop out of the competition. They were missing test players [[Karl Ifwersen]] and [[Dougie McGregor]].\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 14 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 18-13\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Ponsonby Defeats City/Ponsonby V City\n| page =7\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17188\n| date = 1919-06-16\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190616.2.118.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>\n| away = City\n| try1 = S Chatfield, Cadman, Neil, Edwards\n| con1 = E McGregor, D Norgrove 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Paki, R Mitchell, penalty try\n| con2 = Harry Francis 2\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park 1\n| attendance = 7000\n| referee = Eddowes\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 14 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Maritime\n| score = 34-0\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Wins for Maritime and Shore/Maritime V Marist Old Boys\n| page =7\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LVI, Issue 17188\n| date = 1919-06-16\n| url = https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19190616.2.118.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-19}}</ref>\n| away = Marist\n| try1 = [[George Davidson (athlete)|George Davidson]] 4, 