al-parts-mother-maybelle-and-mama-ru |work=The Bluegrass Situation |date=19 May 2017 }}</ref>\n*[[Steven Wilson]]\n*[[Patrick Wolf]]\n*[[Shara Worden]] of [[My Brightest Day]]\n*Martin Molin of [[Wintergatan]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Autoharp players|*]]\n", "name_user": "Tobelaura", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added another notable player of the autoharp", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_autoharp_players"}
{"title_page": "DWLA-TV", "text_new": "{{Infobox broadcast\n|  call_letters             = DWLA-TV (GMA TV-12 Legazpi)\n|  station_logo             = \n|  station_slogan           = Buong Puso Para Sa Kapuso\n|  station_branding         = ''GMA TV-12 Legazpi''\n|  analog                   = 12 ([[VHF]])\n|  founded                  = {{Start date|1982}}\n|  location                 = [[Legazpi, Albay]]\n|  owner                    = [[GMA Network (company)|GMA Network Inc.]]\n|  sister_stations          = DWJB-TV ([[GMA News TV]])<br>DWGE-TV ([[GMA Network|GMA]])<br>[[DWCW|Barangay LS 96.3 Legazpi]]\n|  callsign_meaning         = '''DW'''<br>'''L'''egazpi<br>'''A'''lbay\n|  affiliations             = [[GMA Network]] '''([[owned-and-operated station|O&O]])'''\n|  former_affiliations      = \n|  effective_radiated_power = 10,000 watts<br>(25,000 watts ERP)\n|  homepage                 = [http://www.gmanetwork.com GMANetwork.com]\n}}\n\n'''DWLA-TV''', channel 12 (also known as '''GMA TV-12 Legazpi'''), is a [[Local community|local]] [[Commercial broadcasting|commercial]] [[television station]] in [[Legazpi, Albay]] owned and operated by [[GMA Network (company)|GMA Network Inc.]]. Its transmitter and broadcast facilities are located at Mt. Bariw, Estanza, [[Legazpi, Albay|Legazpi City]]\n\n==GMA TV-12 Legazpi Programs==\n* Word of God Network (Every Sunday 6:00am to 7:00am)\n\n==See also==\n*[[DWCW|Barangay LS 96.3 Legazpi]]\n*[[List of GMA Network stations]]\n\n{{GMA Luzon}}\n\n[[Category:GMA Network stations]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1982]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Albay]]\n\n{{Philippines-tv-stub}}\n{{Tv-station-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox broadcast\n|  call_letters             = DWLA-TV (GMA TV-12 Legazpi)\n|  station_logo             = \n|  station_slogan           = Buong Puso Para Sa Kapuso\n|  station_branding         = ''GMA TV-12 Legazpi''\n|  analog                   = 12 ([[VHF]])\n|  founded                  = {{Start date|1982}}\n|  location                 = [[Legazpi, Albay]]\n|  owner                    = [[GMA Network (company)|GMA Network Inc.]]\n|  sister_stations          = DWJB-TV ([[GMA News TV]])<br>DWGE-TV ([[GMA Network|GMA]])<br>[[DWCW|Barangay LS 96.3 Legazpi]]\n|  callsign_meaning         = '''DW'''<br>'''L'''egazpi<br>'''A'''lbay\n|  affiliations             = [[GMA Network]] '''([[owned-and-operated station|O&O]])'''\n|  former_affiliations      = \n|  effective_radiated_power = 10,000 watts<br>(25,000 watts ERP)\n|  homepage                 = [http://www.gmanetwork.com GMANetwork.com]\n}}\n\n'''DWLA-TV''', channel 12 (also known as '''GMA TV-12 Legazpi'''), is a [[Local community|local]] [[Commercial broadcasting|commercial]] [[television station]] in [[Legazpi, Albay]] owned and operated by [[GMA Network (company)|GMA Network Inc.]]. Its transmitter and broadcast facilities are located at Mt. Bariw, Estanza, [[Legazpi, Albay|Legazpi City]]\n\n==History==\n*'''1982''' - DWLA-TV channel 12, the first television station in Bicol was launched by GMA Network's predecessor Republic Broadcasting System along with the introduction of its ''GMA Radio-Television Arts'' ident with the later used the rainbow colors of red, yellow, green and blue stripes. \n*'''April 30, 1992''' - DWLA-TV officially debuted its ''Rainbow Satellite Network'', the ident served as a relay station of the network's flagship station [[DZBB-TV]] Channel 7 Manila to viewers in Albay and the Bicol region with the utilizes a new logo to correspond with the rebranding and a satellite-beaming rainbow in a multicolored striped based on a traditional scheme of red, orange, green, yellow, blue, indigo and violet, with GMA in a metallic form uses a San Serif Century Gothic Extra Bold and analogous gloominess of Indigo as its fonts in the letters.\n*'''2009''' - GMA launch its sister station (now defunct) QTV Channel 27 Legazpi before re-launched on February 28, 2011 as GMA News TV Channel 27 Legazpi.\n*'''August 10, 2012''' - GMA Naga and Legazpi were upgraded to a \"super station\" and it was called '''GMA Bicol''' in its branding, which primarily covers the provinces of Camarines Sur (via Channel 7) and Albay (via Channel 12).\n*'''September 17, 2012 \u2013 November 7, 2014''' - GMA Bicol launched its flagship local newscast ''Baretang Bikol''.\n*'''November 10, 2014''' - GMA Bicol re-launched its flagship local newscast ''[[24 Oras Bikol]]''.\n* '''April 24, 2015''' - GMA Network decided to cancel airing ''24 Oras Bikol'' as part of the strategic streamlining undertaken by the network. The Bicol stations were now downgraded as a relay (satellite-selling) station.\n*'''October 3, 2016''' - GMA Bicol began to simulcast [[GMA Dagupan]]'s Balitang Amianan.\n\n==GMA TV-12 Legazpi Programs==\n*[[Balitang Amianan]] - flagship afternoon newscast (simulcast on [[DZEA-TV|TV-10 Dagupan]])<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/GMARegionalTV/videos/1181337248598575/]</ref>\n* Word of God Network (Every Sunday 6:00am to 7:00am)\n\n==See also==\n*[[DWCW|Barangay LS 96.3 Legazpi]]\n*[[List of GMA Network stations]]\n\n{{GMA Luzon}}\n\n[[Category:GMA Network stations]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1982]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Albay]]\n\n{{Philippines-tv-stub}}\n{{Tv-station-stub}}\n", "name_user": "2001:4454:2ca:3500:803:8f34:294a:e531", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DWLA-TV"}
